Familiar with a variety of the field's concepts, practices, and procedures.

raw_data.title: Content Editor / Developer
raw_data.description: Responsible for editing and publishing information on websites; developing the agency's content strategy, including the technical aspect of content creation; as well as creating its deliverables. “Content” is a broad term that can refer to blog posts, static web copy, podcasts, and video content.

raw_data.title: Graphic Designer

Produces the highest quality documents, web pages, briefings, videos, conference materials and conceptual art. Coordinates design projects and has excellent communication and organizational skills.

raw_data.title: Narrator
raw_data.description: Professional voice talent responsible for reading the narrative script for recording purposes.

raw_data.title: On-Line Editor
raw_data.description: Oversee the content on websites.  May also need to follow and understand web traffic patterns to glean what content draws more users to the site.  Develops the content or an editorial plan of a certain web site.  Delivers and designs various web campaigns in order to achieve the Agency's goals and objectives with the use of interactive web spaces.  Evaluates the work of the web whether it is successful or not, sets some indicators with key performances, monitors visitor statistics, website feedback as well as participation.  Online editors mostly work with its team which may include a writer, creative director, and web designer, graphic designer and information architect.

raw_data.title: Producer
raw_data.description: Manages the production process interacting with client, crew, and outside vendors. Ensures that the projects are completed on time and on budget delivering a product that meets the client's needs.

raw_data.title: Quality Assurance Specialist
raw_data.description: The Quality Assurance Specialist checks video content and file to make sure that it meets the quality standards from a technical and content policy point of view. The QAS provides a thorough check of the final exported content (usually a trailer). The QAS checks for editorial, color grading, visual effects, on-screen credits and ensures the final mix have all been completed and combined into the final master version of the trailer / video. At the end of the QC process, the Director / Producer is provided with a detailed multi-page report outlining how the master is built, what issues exist with video or audio, and also calling out any potential mistakes or oversights made during earlier stages

raw_data.title: SME, Historian
raw_data.description: The project Historian researches, studies and analyzes the script content for historical, social or cultural significance. They interpret and present theories and information to the director / producer; researches information pertinent to the project via Internet, library, telephone calls, conducts interviews or travel to areas where filming will take place; and reports back to the Producer/Director/Writer in order to facilitate changes necessary to the project. Post production, the Historian catalogs and preserves historically significant documents, records and video for posterity.

raw_data.title: Videographer
raw_data.description: Shoots footage and assists in editing.  Accomplishes the bulk of the technical tasks related to production and post-production. Transports, sets up, and operates equipment; and assists with staging, set preparation and dressing. May use computers and related technologies to create and manipulate electronic images. May design and produce web or desktop multimedia products including graphic design, digital video, audio capture, editing digital and conventional still photography, or hand drawn or computer design. Experience with software required to manipulate electronic images. Generally, works under direct supervision.

raw_data.title: Writer
raw_data.description: The Writer is a skilled at writing the TV; Video or Film story and is responsible for the developing, writing, and revision of scripts. They are responsible for creating all plot lines, characters, dialogue and situations. They usually work as part of a group of writers or team to ensure that scripts are written well; meet industry guidelines; and stays true to the message. Takes direction from the Director to “tell the story” as required by the client..

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Serves as the contractor's single contract manager, and shall be the contractor's authorized interface with the Government Contracting Officer (CO), the contract level Contracting Officer's Representative (COR), government management personnel and customer agency representatives, keeping them fully informed, both verbally and in writing .Responsible for formulating and enforcing work standards, assigning contractor schedules, reviewing work discrepancies, supervising contractor personnel and communicating policies, purposes, and goals of the organization to subordinates. Shall be responsible for the overall contract performance and shall not serve in any other capacity under this contract. Specialized experience includes: complete Information Technology (IT) project development from inception to deployment, demonstrated ability to provide guidance and direction in the tasks similar to the representative scenarios provided in the RFP, proven expertise in the management and control of funds and resources, demonstrated capability in managing multi-task contracts of this type and complexity. General experience includes increasing responsibilities in information systems design and management.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert III
raw_data.description: Serves as source of broad general knowledge of systems engineering, systems analysis and design, software integration, and software development with an in-depth expertise in these areas. Primary function is to perform complex technical efforts in specialty area by serving either as senior technical staff member on a large project or as a leader of a small, specialized project. Other functions are to provide, within the specialty area, quick response problem resolution, internal and external training, and marketing support to translate advanced technology theory into specific, practical applications of use for the corporation. Requires knowledge in a specific professional technical field (such as artificial intelligence, statistics, electronics, computer science, mathematics, or physics) to define and solve new information processing system problems, develop engineering designs, and conduct analyses and experiments in the area of discipline.

raw_data.title: Information Sys Security Officer, I
raw_data.description: Information Systems Security Officer I provides minimally supervised support for difficult analysis and evaluation assignments. Has the ability to provide analysis and consulting to management level personnel. Performs analysis and evaluation of existing or proposed processes, applications, systems, or software. Performs, and/or may direct, project planning, scope, control, management, tracking, or review. May perform functional requirements gathering for projects, to include security requirements. Performs analysis and evaluation throughout the process, application, system, or software development life-cycle which includes, but is not limited to: planning, requirements, design, acquisition, development, integration, installation/ deployment, performance tuning, testing, or training.  Performs, or may direct, document development/ preparation at various stages of a project life-cycle (e.g., planning through implementation) to detail analysis results and solution recommendations.  Assists with testing to support the project life-cycle, as applicable. Uses methodologies, modeling/ estimating techniques, tools, applications, systems, software, or databases at advanced levels to perform assigned tasks.

Provide a periodic training resource analysis report from the analysis of data, system operations, methods, inputs and outputs, and activities to identify gaps in resources, recommend improvements, and coordinate activities to produce a more effective program.
